<dl id="n57070g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n57" href="#n57070g">N57 (VI.B.47)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n57all.htm#n57070g"> 70(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> merrily we / roll along <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n57070g"><li>FW 615.21 </li><li><a href="../../flex/td/lextd.htm#n57070g">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/td/l39td.htm#n57070g">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n57070g">MS BL 47488-214v</ms> </li><li>JJA 63:312 <a name="tad6" href="../../FF/fdra/tda.htm#tdd3">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/td/tdd3.htm#n57070g">Draft: IV&sect;4.3</a> </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Song, <i>Merrily We Roll Along</i>. Also a play by George S. Kaufman and Moss Hart, which opened on Broadway in 1934. The plot concerns the standard story about the gradual disillusionment of a youthful idealist. What was unusual was that this was presented in reverse chronological order.</mm> </dd></dl>
